page.title: 20TRANSPORT
page.content: PUBLIC TRANSPORT IS NOT VERY GOOD AND SO PEOPLE HAVE A CAR.THE BUS SERVICE IS RUN BY UNITED COUNTIES.YOU CAN GET TO MILTON KEYNES IN ONE DIRECTION AND TO WELLINGBOROUGH IN THE OTHER.THERE IS ALSO A BUS TO LONDON THAT PASSES THROUGH THE VILLAGE.IT STARTS FROM CORBY AND COMES THROUGH MORNING AND EVENING ON WEEK DAYS BUT THERE ARE LESS AT WEEKENDS. MANY PEOPLE IN BOZEAT NOW HAVE TWO CARS BECAUSE THERE IS A GREATER TREND FOR MUMS TO GO OUT TO WORK,COUPLED WITH THE POOR BUS SERVICE. THE NEAREST RAILWAY STATIONS ARE AT WELLINGBOROUGH OR NORTHAMPTON..
